This week on Business Day TV’s Editing Allowed Peter Bruce and a panel of editors discuss how the state capture inquiry came to an abrupt halt thanks to the Hawks’ surprise entrance. They also take a look at allegations levelled against Naspers and developments at Steinhoff. South African billionaire and Steinhoff chairman Christo Wiese has personally lost at about R40bn this year, especially in the past three days, since the resignation of Markus Jooste. The Editing Allowed panel take a look at the reasons for Steinhoff’s downfall and whether this could possibly be the end of the company. OR LISTEN TO THE AUDIO: